	(341,1,'2015-08-26 02:20:28','2015-08-26 02:20:28','<!--:en--><div id=\"area-article-first-block\" class=\"area\">\n<div id=\"mod-a-body-first-para\" class=\"mod-economictimesarticletext mod-articletext\">\n\nNEW DELHI: Anyone looking for an affordable, touch-enabled Windows ultraportable laptop is in luck, because Asus decided to launch the VivoBook S200 at a much lower price than the next touch-based competitor.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"mod-a-body-after-first-para\" class=\"mod-economictimesarticletextwithadcpc mod-economictimesarticletext mod-articletext\">\n\n<strong>Price: </strong>Rs 39,990\n\n<strong>Rating:</strong> ****\n\n<strong>Specifications:</strong> 11.6-inch (1366 x 768 pixel) touchscreen, Intel Core i3 processor, 4GB RAM, 500GB HDD, Intel HD 4000, Windows 8, 1.3kg.\n\n<strong>Pros: </strong>Compact, value for money, responsive touchscreen, loud audio output, good battery life.\n\n<strong>Cons:</strong> Poor viewing angles, small function and arrow keys, audible cooling fan noise.\n\n</div><!--:-->','ET Reviews: Asus VivoBook S200','','publish','open','open','','et-reviews-asus-vivobook-s200-2','','','2015-08-26 02:20:28','2015-08-26 02:20:28','',0,'http://asus-zenpad.stagingapps.net/?p=232',0,'post','',0),
	(342,1,'2015-08-26 02:22:25','2015-08-26 02:22:25','<!--:en--><div id=\"area-article-first-block\" class=\"area\">\n<div id=\"mod-a-body-first-para\" class=\"mod-economictimesarticletext mod-articletext\">\n\nASUS has officially unveiled a new 256GB model of theZenFone 2 Deluxe at a dedicated launch event in Sao Paulo, Brazil. This version packs the same hardware as the initially unveiled model and the internal storage is the only differentiating factor here.\n\nThis takes smartphone storage to a whole new level and ensures that users don\'t have to be looking for a microSD card to get more storage on their handset. It is not known as to when the smartphone will be unveiled in the Indian markets, but we\'re guessing that will happen very soon knowing that the ZenFone 2 was one of the first markets where the ZenFone 2 Deluxe was announced and released.\n\n</div>\n</div><!--:-->','ASUS Releases a 256GB Storage','','publish','open','open','','asus-releases-a-256gb-storage-variant-of-the-zenfone-2-deluxe-2','','','2015-08-26 02:22:25','2015-08-26 02:22:25','',0,'http://asus-zenpad.stagingapps.net/?p=235',0,'post','',0),
	(343,1,'2015-08-26 02:25:29','2015-08-26 02:25:29','<!--:en-->You won\'t want to miss out on IFA 2015. Several big giants including Samsung, Huawei, and Sony have already announced their plans for the tradeshow event, and now Asus is also joining the hype train. The Taiwanese technology company teases the launch of a new smartwatch and a new smartphone at a press conference on September 2.\n\nThe company has posted a video on its <a href=\"http://gadgets.ndtv.com/tags/facebook\">Facebook</a> page in which it <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/ASUS/videos/939412919435440/\" target=\"_blank\">teases</a> new products. Among which include a new monitor, a smartphone that appears to have a rear-positioned volume rocker as seen in many of its recent <a href=\"http://gadgets.ndtv.com/tags/zenfone\">ZenFone</a> smartphones.<!--:-->','Asus Set to Launch New Smartphone','','publish','open','open','','asus-set-to-launch-new-smartphone-2','','','2015-08-26 02:25:29','2015-08-26 02:25:29','',0,'http://asus-zenpad.stagingapps.net/?p=238',0,'post','',0),
	(344,1,'2015-08-26 02:29:50','2015-08-26 02:29:50','<!--:en-->Asus, at its ZenFestival event in New Delhi on Thursday, <a href=\"http://gadgets.ndtv.com/mobiles/news/asus-zenfone-2-laser-zenfone-2-deluxe-and-zenfone-selfie-launched-in-india-724761\">showcased</a> new devices including the latest<a href=\"http://gadgets.ndtv.com/asus-zenfone-2-deluxe-2848\">ZenFone 2 Deluxe</a>, <a href=\"http://gadgets.ndtv.com/asus-zenfone-selfie-2670\">ZenFone Selfie</a>, <a href=\"http://gadgets.ndtv.com/asus-zenfone-2-laser-ze550kl-2840\">ZenFone 2 Laser</a>, and <a href=\"http://gadgets.ndtv.com/asus-zenfone-max-2849\">ZenFone Max</a> alongside announcing two new ZenPad tablets - the <a href=\"http://gadgets.ndtv.com/asus-zenpad-7-0-z370cg-2680\">ZenPad 7.0</a> and <a href=\"http://gadgets.ndtv.com/asus-zenpad-8-0-z380kl-2678\">ZenPad 8.0</a>. The new ZenFone smartphones are all in the low to mid-range segment, much like the earlier phones in this series. During the launch, Asus Chairman Jonney Shih said that the company has shipped 1.5 million handsets to India in a year since July last year.<!--:-->','Global Launch Event','','publish','open','open','','asus-shifting-focus-from-laptops-to-smartphones-3','','','2015-08-26 02:29:50','2015-08-26 02:29:50','',0,'http://asus-zenpad.stagingapps.net/?p=244',0,'post','',0),
	(345,1,'2015-08-26 02:32:29','2015-08-26 02:32:29','<!--:en-->Taiwanese electronics major AsusTek\'s chairman Jonney Shih on his maiden visit to India on Thursday said the group was shifting its focus from notebooks to smartphones and convertibles.\n\n\"The PC market is slowly showing signs of decay as the world is moving to a cloud first, mobile first platform. At Asus, we believe in riding the current technology wave and hence in our research and development we are focusing more on devices like convertibles that will provide more productivity and connectivity on the go,\" Jonney Shih told IANS on the sidelines of the Zen Festival where Asus launched three new phones and showcased some tablets.<!--:-->','Asus Shifting Focus From Laptops to Smartphones','','publish','open','open','','asus-shifting-focus-from-laptops-to-smartphones-2-2','','','2015-08-26 02:32:29','2015-08-26 02:32:29','',0,'http://asus-zenpad.stagingapps.net/?p=248',0,'post','',0),
